Core Difference
Visibility → Controls whether a widget is visible, while optionally keeping it in layout
Offstage → Keeps widget built but completely out of layout and painting

========================

Mental Models (Easy to Remember)

Visibility = “Hide in place”
UI is already part of the screen, just hidden
Like turning a feature ON/OFF
Can still occupy space (if configured)
Can preserve state

Visibility = Actor behind a Curtain
What’s happening?
The actor is still on stage
Covered by a curtain
Still:
Standing in same position (takes space)
Remembering lines (state preserved)
Ready to act instantly
You can pull the curtain anytime

*******************************************

Offstage = “Keep it ready, but don’t show”
UI is built but not participating in layout at all
Like preloading a screen in background
No space taken
State is preserved

What’s happening?
Actor is not on stage
Waiting behind the stage
Still:
Knows lines (state preserved)
Fully prepared
BUT:
Not taking any stage space
Audience can’t see them
When needed → actor walks in instantly

==============================

When to Use What
Use Visibility when:
You want to toggle UI frequently
You may want to preserve layout or animations
UI is part of normal screen structure
Use Offstage when:
You want to preload heavy UI
You need widget ready but hidden
You don’t want it affecting layout

